    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix EEA0 encryption handling for partial bytes\n\n### Summary\nThe nas_stream_encrypt_eea0 function in the security module was not properly validating input parameters and had inconsistent bit length handling compared to other EEA implementations. When processing NAS messages with certain bit lengths, the function would attempt to copy more bytes than available, leading to buffer overreads and potential data corruption.\n\nThe root cause was missing input validation and using (blength + 7) >> 3 for byte calculation instead of ensuring bit length was a multiple of 8 like EEA1/EEA2. This caused the function to read beyond the message buffer when blength wasn't aligned to byte boundaries.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/SECU/nas_stream_eea0.c`: Added proper input validation with DevAssert checks for message pointer, minimum length, and bit alignment. Changed byte length calculation to use bit shift only after ensuring 8-bit alignment.\n"
}